{"title_page": "Underground Gaming", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox sports team\n| name = Underground Gaming\n|image = Underground Gaming logo 2018.png\n| short_name = Underground, UGG\n| games = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[Call of Duty]]''\n* ''[[For Honor]]''\n* ''[[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]]''\n* ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (video game series)| Pok\u00e9mon]]''\n* ''[[Super Smash Bros.]]''\n* ''[[Tekken]]''\n* ''[[Rocket League]]''\n}}\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2018|11|15}}\n| location = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]].\n}}\n| colors = {{color box|#E30022}} {{color box|#000000}}\n| owntitle = Owners\n| owner = {{List collapsed|title=''See list''|1= Khaled Sadeq \u00b7 Bader Al-Fahad \u00b7 Hussain Al-Qallaf \u00b7 Salem Rajab \u00b7 Basil Al-Mansour \u00b7 Jarrah Al-Deekan \u00b7 Mohammed Abdulreda \u00b7 Abdulhameed Ghassan \u00b7 Abdullah Ashkanani \u00b7 Mohammed Al-Falakawi\n}}\n| ceo = Khaled Sadeq\n| president =\n| partners = {{Plainlist|\n* Q8 Collectibles\n* Joystixx arcade & Bar\n}}\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Underground Gaming''' is a professional [[ESports|esports]] <ref>https://play.eslgaming.com/team/15205157/</ref> and [[entertainment]] organization headquartered in [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]]. Founded on November 15th, 2018. The organization started works in mid 2019 organizing tournaments across the country in hopes to put the organizations name to be recognized  and recruit players. The team currently has players in [[Call of Duty]], [[Tom Clancy's Rainbow Six Siege]], [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]], [[Super Smash Bros.]], [[Tekken]] and [[Rocket League]].\n\n==History==\nAs one of the first major Esport teams to be established in the country. The team was founded by Khaled Sadeq and Bader Al-Fahad on November 15th, 2018 and took off on the social platform [[Instagram]] 9 days later <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BqkT_zchnVw/?igshid=ss53mv1i3kgr |publisher=Instagram.com|title=Underground Gaming Launch Instagram|accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref>. Along with the co-founders, 8 other members later joined instantly with major roles. Being the last member to join So far, Mohammed Abdulreda joined the team in late last September 2019. The team started playing in mid 2019 first helping organize a [[Super Smash Bros.|smash]] tournament and winning 3rd place along side the accolades of having top players in [[For Honor]]. \nLater in October 2019, launching their [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]] Pro clubs team to compete in that game mode. At the end of 2019 they launched their youtube channel but yet to have any content uploaded as of today, along side having annual Player awards <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B7N-njQHyQV/?igshid=9jqlnbk2qov |publisher=Instagram.com|title=Tekken Tournament Instagram|accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\n2020 saw the team focusing more on developing the organization and working on projects for gamers and future content creators, not just players <ref>{{cite web|url= https://twitter.com/uground_gaming/status/1209433801509801984?s=21 |publisher=Twitter.com|title=Announce Award|accessdate=30 November 2019}}</ref>. As support of helping people to stay at home during [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] the team announced an online tournament the '''Underground Pro Clubs Cup''' and invitational [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA Pro clubs tournament]] and announce it will be an annual tournament.\n\n==Achievements and Honors==\n\n===FIFA===\n====Domestic====\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Premier League''':\n:: 2019\u201320<ref>https://challonge.com/n6s0b4m6/standings</ref>\n\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Cup''':\n:: 2019\u201320<ref> https://www.instagram.com/p/B9cstmWhQiQ/?igshid=1v2y84ar58n8i</ref>\n\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Super Cup''':\n:: 2020 <ref> https://www.instagram.com/p/B92XN-9hcgC/ </ref>\n\n===Super Smash Bros.===\n====Domestic====\n*'''Super Smash Bros. Summer League''':\n:: 2019\n\n*'''Kuwait Comic Con Smash Bros. Tournament''':\n:: 2020\n\n== Roster & Personnel ==\n\n=== Management ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! ID\n! Name\n! Role\n|-\n| -\n|{{Flagicon|Kuwait}} Khaled Sadeq\n| CEO\n|-\n| Sharbaka\n|{{Flagicon|Kuwait}} Hussain Al-Qallaf\n| Vice President\n|-\t\n| REB\n|{{Flagicon|Kuwait}} Bader Al-Fahad\n| Head of Media\n|-\n|-\n|}\n\n== Tournaments & Events ==\n\n* ''' Super Smash Underground Open''':\nAn annual [[Super Smash Bros.]] event organized by Underground Gaming, first agreed upon after helping organize multiple Smash events across summer of 2019, the first event was held on August 27 2019. \n\n* ''' Underground Pro Clubs Cup ''':\nAn annual [[FIFA series|FIFA pro clubs]] online tournament held by Underground Gaming, first announced on March 15 2020 in terms with the vision of persuading people to stay at home with [[COVID-19]] that happened that year.\n\n==Sponsorships & Partners==\n* ''' Q8 Collecitbles''': A toy and collectibles online businesses, first announced on June 2 2019 by both parties on social media platforms <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.instagram.com/p/ByMEH1wHSz1/?igshid=g7ekhk8ws83u |publisher=Q8 Collectibles| title=Q8 Collectibles announcement |accessdate=29 June 2019}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.instagram.com/p/ByLrk0oFccd/?igshid=1sphaxq9pn4lp |publisher=Instagram.com|title=Underground Gaming Announcement|accessdate=29 June 2019}}</ref> . Following sponsoring Events and organizing along the team.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://twitter.com/uground_gaming Official Twitter]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/under.gaming Official Instagram]\n\n{{Sports governing bodies in Kuwait}}\n{{Esports competitions}}\n\n[[Category:2018 establishments in Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Esports teams based in the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Esports teams based in Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Sports teams based in Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Esports teams established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Sports clubs established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Esports teams]]\n{{Esports-organization-stub}}\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox sports team\n| name = Underground Gaming\n|image = Underground Gaming logo 2018.png\n| short_name = Underground, UGG\n| games = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[Call of Duty]]''\n* ''[[For Honor]]''\n* ''[[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]]''\n* ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (video game series)| Pok\u00e9mon]]''\n* ''[[Super Smash Bros.]]''\n* ''[[Tekken]]''\n* ''[[Rocket League]]''\n}}\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2018|11|15}}\n| location = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]].\n}}\n| colors = {{color box|#E30022}} {{color box|#000000}}\n| owntitle = Owners\n| owner = {{List collapsed|title=''See list''|1= Khaled Sadeq \u00b7 Bader Al-Fahad \u00b7 Hussain Al-Qallaf \u00b7 Salem Rajab \u00b7 Basil Al-Mansour \u00b7 Jarrah Al-Deekan \u00b7 Mohammed Abdulreda \u00b7 Abdulhameed Ghassan \u00b7 Abdullah Ashkanani \u00b7 Mohammed Al-Falakawi\n}}\n| ceo = Khaled Sadeq\n| president =\n| partners = {{Plainlist|\n* Q8 Collectibles\n* Joystixx arcade & Bar\n}}\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Underground Gaming''' is a professional [[ESports|esports]] <ref>https://play.eslgaming.com/team/15205157/</ref> and [[entertainment]] organization headquartered in [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]]. Founded on November 15th, 2018. The organization started works in mid 2019 organizing tournaments across the country in hopes to put the organizations name to be recognized  and recruit players. The team currently has players in [[Call of Duty]], [[Tom Clancy's Rainbow Six Siege]], [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]], [[Super Smash Bros.]], [[Tekken]] and [[Rocket League]].\n\n==History==\nAs one of the first major Esport teams to be established in the country. The team was founded by Khaled Sadeq and Bader Al-Fahad on November 15th, 2018 and took off on the social platform [[Instagram]] 9 days later <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.instagram.com/p/BqkT_zchnVw/?igshid=ss53mv1i3kgr |publisher=Instagram.com|title=Underground Gaming Launch Instagram|accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref>. Along with the co-founders, 8 other members later joined instantly with major roles. Being the last member to join So far, Mohammed Abdulreda joined the team in late last September 2019. The team started playing in mid 2019 first helping organize a [[Super Smash Bros.|smash]] tournament and winning 3rd place along side the accolades of having top players in [[For Honor]]. \nLater in October 2019, launching their [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]] Pro clubs team to compete in that game mode. At the end of 2019 they launched their youtube channel but yet to have any content uploaded as of today, along side having annual Player awards <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B7N-njQHyQV/?igshid=9jqlnbk2qov |publisher=Instagram.com|title=Tekken Tournament Instagram|accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\n2020 saw the team focusing more on developing the organization and working on projects for gamers and future content creators, not just players <ref>{{cite web|url= https://twitter.com/uground_gaming/status/1209433801509801984?s=21 |publisher=Twitter.com|title=Announce Award|accessdate=30 November 2019}}</ref>. As support of helping people to stay at home during [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] the team announced an online tournament the '''Underground Pro Clubs Cup''' and invitational [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA Pro clubs tournament]] and announce it will be an annual tournament.\n\n==Achievements and Honors==\n\n===FIFA===\n====Domestic====\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Premier League''':\n:: 2019\u201320<ref>https://challonge.com/n6s0b4m6/standings</ref>\n\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Cup''':\n:: 2019\u201320<ref> https://www.instagram.com/p/B9cstmWhQiQ/?igshid=1v2y84ar58n8i</ref>\n\n* '''Q8C pro clubs Super Cup''':\n:: 2020 <ref> https://www.instagram.com/p/B92XN-9hcgC/ </ref>\n\n===Super Smash Bros.===\n====Domestic====\n*'''Super Smash Bros. Summer League''':\n:: 2019\n\n*'''Kuwait Comic Con Smash Bros. Tournament''':\n:: 2020\n\n== R